      "content": "That phrasing is indeed very broad and should make you cautious. It means that if any outside party sues the client because of your work, you could be financially responsible for their defense costs and any resulting judgment. It's not just about what you actively did wrong; it covers claims arising from your performance. You should try to negotiate this clause to make sure it only covers claims directly caused by your negligence or breach of contract.",
